liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Victorians are set to learn the details of a long-awaited housing shake-up to address weak supply and soaring rents. Premier Daniel Andrews and his ministers met yesterday to endorse the first lot of reforms ahead of an expected announcement as early as today. The changes are expected to include an Australian-first consumer tax on short-term accommodation bookings with providers like Airbnb and Stayz. They're also expected to include incentives to build social housing.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Hot and dry conditions are expected to persist across northern and eastern New South Wales today. It comes on the back of the Bureau of Meteorology formally declaring an El Ni√±o weather event is underway. Total fire bans include Newcastle, Lake Macquarie, Port Stephens and parts of the state's Central West. Meanwhile, a severe weather warning remains in place for parts of Tasmania. Firefighters are continuing to battle a bushfire on the state's east coast that forced the evacuation of residents in Coles Bay overnight .
